&lt;p>Keep in mind, that we also organize a workshop about this topic: &lt;a href="https://perspectives-ws.github.io/2022/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">PERSPECTIVES 2022&lt;/a> (which will be collocated with &lt;a href="https://recsys.acm.org/recsys22/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">RecSys 2022&lt;/a>).&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Co-Chair of PERSPECTIVES 2022</title><link>https://chbeu.github.io/post/20220414_perspectives/</link><pubDate>Thu, 14 Apr 2022 17:35:06 +0200</pubDate><guid>https://chbeu.github.io/post/20220414_perspectives/</guid><description>&lt;p>The workshop &lt;a href="https://perspectives-ws.github.io/2022/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Perspectives on the Evaluation of Recommender Systems&lt;/a> is back at &lt;a href="https://recsys.acm.org/recsys22/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">RecSys 2022&lt;/a>. I am happy to co-chair this workshop together with &lt;a href="https://evazangerle.at" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Eva Zangerle&lt;/a> and &lt;a href="https://www.alansaid.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Alan Said&lt;/a>. The &lt;a href="https://perspectives-ws.github.io/2022/#cfp" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Call for Papers&lt;/a> and the submission details are already available at the workshop website.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Slides for UMAP 2021 tutorial</title><link>https://chbeu.github.io/post/_posts_wordpress/2021-06-25-slides-for-umap-2021-tutorial/</link><pubDate>Fri, 25 Jun 2021 20:17:54 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://chbeu.github.io/post/_posts_wordpress/2021-06-25-slides-for-umap-2021-tutorial/</guid><description>&lt;p>I enjoyed today&amp;rsquo;s tutorial on multi-method evaluation for adaptive systems at UMAP 2021. The slides are online under the menu point &lt;a href="https://christinebauer.eu/?page_id=124#tutorials" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Teaching&lt;/a>.&lt;/p>
